question: Will SVB be acquired by Monday night?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if announcement that Silicon Valley Bank (SVB) will be, has been, or is being acquired or merged with between by March 13, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purposes of this market, an announcement by SVB is enough to trigger a "Yes" resolution, regardless of whether the announced acquisition/merger actually occurs. An announcement that a majority of its assets are being acquired suffices to resolve this market to "Yes." The FDIC acquiring institution doesn't count for this market.

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from Silicon Valley Bank, an acquirer of Silicon Valley Bank, a company merging with SVB, and/or the FDIC, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question: Will $USDC depeg by March 31?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if USDC was below 98 cents for 12 consecutive hours (namely it never reached .980000 or above during the 12h period) between March 9 and March 31, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET.

If USDC was below 98 cents for a 12 hour period starting on the last day, e.g. March 31, 9:00 PM ET to April 1, 9:00 AM ET, this market will still resolve to "Yes."

The resolution source for this market will be a consensus of credible, highly liquid sources for the price of USDC.

question: Will Coinbase resume USDC redemptions by Monday night?
description:
On Friday, March 10, Coinbase sent out the following statement: "We are temporarily pausing USDC:USD conversions over the weekend while banks are closed. During periods of heightened activity, conversions rely on USD transfers from the banks that clear during normal banking hours. When banks open on Monday, we plan to re-commence conversions."

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Coinbase resumes USDC:USD conversions by March 13, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No."

question: Will $USDC repeg by March 31?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if USDC is 98 cents or above for 6 consecutive hours (namely it never hit .979999 or below during the 6h period) between March 11, 10:00 AM ET and March 31, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET.

If USDC was 98 cents or above for a 6 hour period starting on the last day, e.g. March 31, 9:00 PM ET to April 1, 3:00 AM ET, this market will still resolve to "Yes."

The resolution source for this market will be a consensus of credible, highly liquid sources for the price of USDC.
